<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871021-0106 </DOCNO><HL> Affiliate of SamsonEnergy Buys InterestsIn Wells From Apache</HL><DD> 10/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SAM APA APPTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)NATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG)PETROLEUM (PET) </IN><DATELINE> TULSA, Okla.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Samson Energy Co. said its Samson Resources affiliate acquired interests in 109 producing gas wells and associated acreage from Apache Corp., Apache Petroleum Co. and certain other entities for about $16 million.    Apache Corp. is the general partner of Apache Petroleum, which is a limited partnership with interests in oil and gas. Both are based in Denver. Samson Resources and Samson Properties Inc., the general partner of Samson Energy, are both units of Samson Investment Co., Tulsa.    Samson Energy said the properties, in Oklahoma and Arkansas, have estimated reserves of about 22.2 billion cubic feet of natural gas and 14,300 barrels of oil.    Samson Energy, an oil and gas master limited partnership, said it plans to acquire a portion of the total interest acquired by Samson Resources, contingent upon Samson Energy securing adequate financing, which will add estimated reserves of about 10.2 billion cubic feet of natural gas to its reserve base. </TEXT></DOC>